programme.title: Come Dine with Me

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Magician David J Marks hosts the third dinner party in Ipswich, and hopes to win over Kerrie Pankhurst after offending her the previous night. programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: DJ Dave James hosts the fourth dinner party from Ipswich and asks his guests to attend dressed as pop stars. Claire Flatt and Nicki Yucel are suspicious about his celebrity connections, and there is trouble when the diners discover Dave obtained help with the cooking.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Speed-dating expert Nikki Yucel hosts the final dinner party in Ipswich, and is determined to cultivate a romantic atmosphere. As the evening progresses, Kerrie Pankhurst reveals her feelings for another diner, before the winner of the £1,000 prize is announced.(n)

programme.title: The Dog Who Saved the Holidays
programme.desc: Crimebusting Labrador Zeus enjoys a Christmas break in California when his owner goes to stay with his aunt at her beach house. Zeus is jealous when his master gets a new puppy as a present, but the two dogs must work together when a pair of old enemies are up to no good. Comedy sequel, starring Shelley Long and Gary Valentine.(n)

programme.title: Couples Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Three couples from Birmingham compete to win the £1,000 prize, including Helen and her husband Lorne, who aim to channel their 24 years together into a safe, solid menu. However, lovebirds Ciaran and Anita criticise the food for lacking passion, and try to spice things up. Meanwhile, Rob is so entranced by his Lithuanian wife Egle that he regularly feels the need to pinch himself whenever he looks at her.(n)

programme.title: Location, Location, Location
programme.desc: Phil Spencer tries to persuade City workers Sarah and Ian, who are searching for a home in Balham to consider other areas of London if they are to find a property with the kind of space they desire. Kirstie Allsopp also has a location problem as she helps legal executive Jemma, whose dreams of living near Wimbledon Common seem unrealistic on a budget of £180,000.(n)

programme.title: The Restoration Man
programme.desc: Marco and Kath Walker have bought a pair of 17th and 18th-century cow barns from a local farmer in Wellington, Herefordshire, but the couple are restoration novices and the project is beset with problems from the start. Architect George Clarke offers much-needed advice and discovers how these Grade II-listed buildings and the surrounding land helped to revolutionise cattle farming in the UK.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Home or Away
programme.desc: Graham Hartridge and Maggie Rogers have been together for 18 months and fancy an adventure. He would love to buy a place in the south-west of France, but she is nervous of taking the plunge and would prefer Devon - much closer to family and friends. Jasmine Harman and Jonnie Irwin help with their property search.(n)

programme.title: Lego's Big Christmas
programme.desc: Documentary going behind the scenes in the run-up to the opening of the world's biggest Lego store in London's Leicester store, following Duncan - Britain's only certified Lego professional - who is attempting to build a giant model of Tower Bridge using nearly six million bricks. The film also meets Sophie and Michael, two adult fans who unashamedly maintain their love for the brick, and designer Justin, whose first kit - a re-imagining of The Beatles' Yellow Submarine - prepares to hit the shelves.(n)

programme.title: Posh Pawn
programme.desc: James takes his team for an ice-breaking Christmas excursion with jewellery expert Ian. A luxury yacht moored in London's most exclusive location comes up for sale for £200,000, and Lawrence and James are put through their paces by Britain's most successful female gymnast, Beth Tweddle. She wants to sell her Olympic leotards to raise money for a good cause.(n)

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: The documentary charting the work of staff at St George's A&E continues, this time focusing on the stories of patients whose friendships have seen them through good times and bad. Phil, a 60-year-old bricklayer, is rushed in after suffering multiple injuries following a short fall from a ladder at work, and his business partner Paul discusses how the pair bonded over the course of 28 years. Meanwhile, 93-year-old widow Violet arrives after fracturing her leg while preparing to go out for lunch with the friends who have supported her since the death of her husband, and 18-year-old dance student Shiana comes to A&E with her mother and her best friend, after injuring her ankle during a rehearsal.(n)

programme.title: 8 Out of 10 Cats Does Countdown
programme.sub-title: 8 Out of 10 Cats Does Countdown Christmas Special.
programme.desc: Jimmy Carr hosts this festive edition of the comedy panel show's twist of the words and numbers quiz, with actress Kathy Burke and comedian Russell Howard joining team captains Sean Lock and Jon Richardson. Joe Lycett joins Susie Dent in Dictionary Corner, while Joe Wilkinson `assists' maths whizz Rachel Riley at the numbers board.(n)

programme.title: Father Ted
programme.sub-title: Father Ted Christmas Special: A Christmassy Ted.
programme.desc: This festive episode from 1996 finds the Craggy Island clerics and six other priests lost in what seems to be the world's largest lingerie department, with only Ted's quick thinking preventing the Catholic Church being rocked by a major scandal. His bravery earns him the coveted Golden Cleric award, which is when his troubles really begin. Comedy, starring Dermot Morgan, Ardal O'Hanlon and Frank Kelly.(n)

programme.title: Father Ted

programme.title: Father Ted

programme.title: Gogglebox
programme.desc: A look back at some of the highlights of this year's series, featuring regular armchair presenters Leon and June, Christopher and Stephen, and the Michaels family offering their thoughts on popular and topical TV shows.(n)

programme.title: Very British Problems
programme.desc: A one-off return for the light-hearted show in which comedians and other famous faces reveal how they struggle against that unique combination of being a Brit facing up to all that 21st-century life throws at them - only this time they're complaining about the festive season and all it brings. Julia Walters narrates, while the likes of David Tennant, James Corden, Romesh Ranganathan, Catherine Tate and Danny Dyer ponder how much to give carol singers, how to leave a party early and bad singing during midnight mass - with US comic Rich Hall giving an outsider's view of how daft Brits can be.(n)

programme.title: Travel Man: 48 Hours in
programme.desc: Rebel Wilson joins Richard Ayoade on a rapid-fire tour of the Italian city, taking in as much as they can in just two days. They race past iconic works of art including Botticelli's Venus and Michelangelo's David, take in some street art, go on a rafting trip down the River Arno, climb to the top of the city's cathedral and dine on a traditional tripe sandwich.(n)

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Home or Away
programme.desc: Jasmine Harman and Laura Hamilton offer their help to Margaret Wagstaff and Keith Turner, who want to spend their retirement somewhere other than Aylesbury, Buckinghamshire, but are unable to decide whether they will get more for their money in Cornwall or Collioure, south-west France. programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Home or Away

programme.title: We're Going on a Bear Hunt
programme.desc: Animated adventure, based on the popular children's bedtime book of the same name, by Michael Rosen. Stan, Katie, Rosie, Max and the baby, along with Rufus the dog, all embark on a quest to find some bears. Trekking through whirling snowstorms, muddy bogs and dark forests, the siblings refuse to let anything get in their way. programme.desc: Furniture-maker Jamie Brown has big ideas about turning a colossal Second World War RAF bunker into his new home. Architect George Clarke helps tackle this huge undertaking and discovers the important role the bunker played in the Blitz.(n)

programme.title: What Britain Bought in 2016
programme.desc: Mary Portas conducts a new survey into Britain's spending habits, setting out to determine whether the national events of the past year have altered the way people in the UK part with their cash. Estimates suggest the UK spends £7billion a week, and Mary catches up with representatives from John Lewis, Maplin, Waterstones, ASOS, Superdrug, Hobbycraft and Waitrose to find out how these retailers have fared. She also meets retail forecasters, who cast their eyes back over some of the must-have items, improbable hits and woeful trends of the past 12 months.(n)

programme.title: Guy Martin: Cycling Home for Christmas
programme.desc: The bike enthusiast takes on his longest and hardest challenge yet as he cycles around the entire coast of Great Britain in just 20 days. It's a total of 4,800 miles and to break the world record, which has stood since 1984, he will have to cover 240 miles every day - twice the length of the average Tour de France stage. This documentary follows Guy's preparation as he uncovers how much he will need to eat and sleep, learns about the extreme weather he will face, and meets with expert bike builders. His adventure begins in his home town of Kirmington in the early hours of Sunday December 4th and cameras follow his progress from thereon in.(n)

programme.title: The Big Fat Quiz of the Year 2016

programme.title: Autopsy: The Last Hours Of
programme.sub-title: Autopsy: The Last Hours of Elvis Presley.
programme.desc: Forensic pathologist Dr Richard Shepherd re-examines picks through the facts surrounding Elvis Presley's demise at his Memphis home Graceland in August 1977 at the age of 42, using testimony from the singer's childhood best friend, his cousin and his private nurse, as well as the medical facts. The post-mortem report reveals that towards the end of his life, nearly all of Presley's vital organs were almost twice the size they should have been, and that his system was full of prescription drugs.(n)

programme.title: Who Wants to Be a Millionaire
programme.desc: Although the once-hot game show Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? had lost its luster as a prime-time ABC offering, the producers felt that there was enough life left in the property to warrant a Monday-through-Friday syndicated version. Taking over from the earlier series' host Regis Philbin was Meredith Vieira of The View. To make certain that the series would not be bankrupted after its first week on the air, the questions posed to contestants were considerably harder than those on the prime-time incarnation. Also, the famous "fastest finger" round was eliminated, taking some of the pressure off the contestants when they struggled to come up with answers. The most noteworthy change from the original version was the absence of Regis Philbin's familiar catchphrases: One would never hear Meredith Vieira chime in with the legendary "Is that your final answer?" The syndicated Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? was launched on September 16, 2002(n)

programme.desc: Tim Burton called his interpretation of the classic film a 're-imagining' and it incorporates both stunning visual effects and very human (and simian) emotions. Mark Wahlberg plays astronaut Leo Davidson, whipped through space and time to a 'world' where apes and gorillas rule the humans. Captured, he is nurtured by Ari (Helena Bonham Carter) and hunted by General Thade (Tim Roth) as he leads a rebel group of humans and chimpanzees in search of his downed craft. This is his only hope of escape and, ironically, the planet's only hope of shaking off the tyranny of the gorillas, allowing peaceful humans and chimpanzees to co-exist. programme.title: Resident Evil
programme.desc: The director of Mortal Kombat (1995) adapts another popular video game for the big screen with this gory action thriller. Milla Jovovich and Michelle Rodriguez star as Alice and Rain, two members of a commando team assigned to infiltrate the Hive, an underground research laboratory owned by the faceless conglomerate known as the Umbrella Corporation. programme.desc: Sniper Rifles. The cable documentary series Weaponology investigates the science of warfare as it has progressed and developed - over the centuries - from crude battlefield contraptions to diabolically inventive weaponry. Each episode hones in on one particular category of weapon and discusses its historical evolution and strategic employment on the front lines. The episode entitled "sniper rifles" discusses the background and use of the titular guns, designed to pick off human targets from a lengthy and safe vantage point. The program spans the entire history of the sniper rifle, from the German Jaegers of the 1700s to the Barrett AS50 of the 21th century, and reveals how weaponry has enabled snipers to now shoot at a distance of over 2,000 yards. Subtopics include sights, camouflage, bullets, sniper techniques and much more(n)

programme.title: EastEnders
programme.desc: As Ronnie's big day approaches, she encourages Roxy to build bridges with Jack as the sisters secretly make plans. However, Roxy is later left to look after Ricky and Amy alone - but things do not go well.(n)

Action adventure sequel, updating the series to a personality Cold War setting, starring Harrison Ford, Cate Blanchett, Shia LaBeouf, Ray Winstone and John Hurt.(n)

programme.title: Breakfast
programme.desc: Round-up of national and international news, plus the latest from the money markets.(n)

But Oscar soon finds himself out of his depth as his fearsome reputation gets out of control. Animated comedy, with the voices of Will Smith, Robert De Niro, Martin Scorsese, Renee Zellweger, Angelina Jolie and Jack Black.(n)

programme.title: Wallace & Gromit: The Wrong Trousers
programme.desc: Nick Park's Oscar-winning animation featuring the bumbling inventor and his faithful dog, whose lives are turned upside down after foolishly offering board and lodgings to villainous penguin Feathers McGraw. With the voice of Peter Sallis.(n)

Animated comedy, with the voices of Hugh Jackman, Kate Winslet, Ian McKellen, Shane Richie, Jean Reno and Bill Nighy.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt

programme.title: The Moonstone

It falls to Po to defeat him, but he suffers strange flashbacks revealing a connection between his past and the sinister bird. Animated comedy sequel, with the voices of Jack Black and Gary Oldman.(n)

programme.title: Stick Man

It follows the title character on an incredible adventure across the seasons as he runs from a playful dog, gets thrown into a river, escapes from a swan's nest and even ends up on top of a fire. Will he ever get back to his family in time for Christmas? Martin Freeman heads the voice cast as Stick Man, with Hugh Bonneville, Russell Tovey, Rob Brydon and Sally Hawkins, plus Jennifer Saunders as the narrator.(n)

programme.title: Wreck-It Ralph
programme.desc: A video game villain grows tired of always being the bad guy, and ventures into other games in search of the chance to be a hero, unwittingly causing chaos in the process. When a deadly threat to the entire arcade appears, it falls to him to set things right. Animated adventure, with the voices of John C Reilly, Sarah Silverman and Jane Lynch.(n)

programme.title: Pointless

At the end of each round, the team with the most points is eliminated until the final two pairs battle for the chance to compete for a cash prize. Presented by Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman.(n)

programme.title: Celebrity Mastermind
programme.desc: John Humphrys quizzes another four famous faces on their specialist subjects. Those braving the black chair are Outnumbered actor Tyger Drew-Honey, radio presenter Tom Ravenscroft, actress Maria McErlane and writer of the Horrible History books Terry Deary. The quartet are quizzed on TV comedy The Office, Warp Records, socialite Unity Mitford and GK Chesterton's Father Brown stories respectively.(n)

programme.title: A Question of Sport
programme.desc: Sue Barker asks the questions in the light-hearted quiz, with Formula 1 world champion Nico Rosberg, track cycling legend Chris Hoy, former hurdler Colin Jackson and winter Olympian Amy Williams joining team captains Matt Dawson and Phil Tufnell in such rounds as Sporting Legends and Football Pundits.(n)

programme.title: EastEnders
programme.desc: The events of the past few months finally come to a head for Lee as he reaches breaking point. Max's return continues to cause friction in the Square as loyalties and motives are questioned. Over at the party, Roxy gets jealous when Donna and Shrimpy grow closer.(n)

programme.title: Captain America: The Winter Soldier
programme.desc: Premiere. The superhuman soldier becomes an operative for secret intelligence agency SHIELD, but grows suspicious of their motives. Following a battle with a mysterious cyborg assassin, he and fellow Avenger Black Widow become fugitives, and try to bring down a sinister conspiracy. Comic-book thriller sequel, starring Chris Evans, Scarlett Johansson, Samuel L Jackson and Robert Redford.(n)

programme.title: Still Game
programme.desc: Festive episode of the popular Scottish comedy, in which Jack and Victor face the prospect of a gloomy Hogmanay stuck in the lift at Osprey Heights, and console themselves by recalling New Years past. As the clock ticks down to 2007, Winston is also in a reminiscent mood, and takes refuge in memories of a legendary holiday season when Craigland really knew how to throw a party. Ford Kiernan, Greg Hemphill and Paul Riley star.(n)

programme.title: Mrs Brown's Boys
programme.sub-title: Mrs Brown's Boys Christmas Special: Mammy's Christmas Punch.
programme.desc: The doting mother-of-six is determined to have a safe and peaceful Christmas at home this year. However, with Mark and Betty arguing about the reappearance of his first love Bubbles, carol singers haunting her every waking hour and Buster installing a new Christmas tree with a very unusual safety feature, how will she manage to survive? The first of two festive instalments of the comedy, written by and starring Brendan O'Carroll, with Danny O'Carroll and featuring a guest appearance by Slade frontman Noddy Holder.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: Documentary following Baghani, a tigress chosen to breed in the wild. She is airlifted from her home in an Indian park to a new reserve where she encounters Rajore, a male who has also recently been released. The pair are filmed over two years, as they fight leopards for territory and learn to hunt boar, while trying to avoid being killed by poachers.(n)

programme.title: Coastal Path
programme.desc: Explorer Paul Rose sets off from Ladram Bay, heading for the chalk cliffs of Beer Head in South Devon. Here John Scott takes him underground on a tour of Beer Quarry caves, where until a few years ago limestone had been extracted for almost 2,000 years. Continuing along the coastal path to Charmouth, he learns about fossil hunting and ammonites and after enjoying the wild orchids in the ancient wildflower meadows of West Hay farm, begins the steep climb up to Golden Cap, the highest point on the path with stunning views along the Jurassic Coast. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: London and South East hopefuls Ronnie Murray, Russell Bateman and Mark Froydenlund serve up their desserts in a last bid to make it through to the regional final. Competing for a place on Friday's judging table are a complex pudding, a challenging take on afternoon tea, and a dessert using the delicate fragrant flavours and spices from the Commonwealth Island of Grenada.(n)

programme.title: Herbie Goes Bananas

Separated from his latest owners, he teams up with a young pickpocket to run a taxi service, and together they uncover a smuggling ring. The fourth part of the Disney adventure series, starring Cloris Leachman, Charles Martin Smith and Joaquin Garay.(n)

programme.title: This Farming Life
programme.desc: Sybil prepares for George's 50th birthday and the arrival of her sister and niece from England, while persistent rain means Martin's cattle are yet to be turned out of their winter sheds into the fields. Bobby and Anne hold an open day to educate the public about farming and John has to urgently call the vet when one of his heifers gets into difficulty calving.(n)

programme.title: Money for Nothing
programme.desc: Sarah Moore transforms four more reclaimed items with the help of designers Jay Blades, Bex Simon and Guy Trench. Arthur Smith narrates.(n)

programme.title: A Distant Trumpet

He is soon tempted away from his fiancee by his commanding officer's wife and also has to resolve the conflict with a rebellious Native American chief. Western, starring Troy Donahue and Suzanne Pleshette.(n)

programme.title: Hidalgo
programme.desc: A former pony express rider appearing in Buffalo Bill's Wild West Show is invited by a wealthy sheikh to take part in a legendary 3,000-mile horse race across the Arabian desert. However, his rivals in the contest are determined not to see a foreigner win, and he is also drawn into political intrigue as the sheikh's enemies plot to steal his horse-breeding secrets. Period adventure, with Viggo Mortensen and Omar Sharif.(n)

programme.title: Nature's Weirdest Events
programme.desc: Chris Packham finds out about the much-loved dolphin that has started breaking people's bones, asks why a caterpillar wears a hat made of its own spare heads, and reveals how a tiny crustacean has mastered the holy grail of science - the art of invisibility.(n)

programme.title: Inside the Factory
programme.desc: Gregg Wallace follows 27 tons of potatoes from a Hampshire farm through the world's largest crisp factory as they are peeled, sliced and fried to make more than five million packets every 24 hours. Cherry Healey discovers the special varieties of potato that are grown to make the snacks, as well the surprising ways that brains can be tricked into thinking a crisp is crunchier than it is. And historian Ruth Goodman investigates who invented the crisp - was it the Americans, as is often cited, or the British?.(n)

programme.title: Tribes, Predators & Me
programme.desc: Gordon Buchanan travels to Papua New Guinea, where he meets a tribe on the banks of the Sepik River that has learned to live alongside crocodiles. Members of the tribe teach him to hunt fully grown adult predators using only their bare hands and discovers their belief that a giant crocodile lives in a nearby lake and protects them from harm. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: New Zealand: Earth's Mythical Islands
programme.desc: New Zealand is now home to some of the richest agricultural land in the world, boasting magnificent gardens with plants from around the planet and rare magical creatures. A caving expedition reveals relics of the original lost world of its pre-human past; the actual bones of a cow-sized flightless grazing bird, a moa, among the largest birds that has ever lived. However, as narrator Sam Neill reveals, against all the odds, one giant bird from primeval New Zealand has survived to this day. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: To the Manor Born
programme.sub-title: To the Manor Born: 1979 Christmas Special: Christmas Special '79.

programme.title: Christmas University Challenge

programme.title: Robot Wars

Paralympic gold medallist Kadeena Cox, football star Robbie Savage, history presenter Neil Oliver and Rizzle Kicks singer Jordan Stephens design their dream robot with the help of an experienced engineer, then battle one another in the arena. Who will become the Celebrity Robot Wars champion?.(n)

programme.title: Charlie Brooker's 2016 Wipe
programme.desc: The writer and broadcaster takes a satirical look back at the events of the past 12 months, a year that has seen the deaths of countless cultural icons, Donald Trump being voted into the White House and the BBC losing the rights to Great British Bake Off. Charlie is joined by the ever-insightful Philomena Cunk, who faces her most challenging interview yet as she tries to get some sense out of Professor Brian Cox.(n)

programme.title: Cunk on Christmas
programme.desc: The commentator from Weekly Wipe examines the true meaning of Christmas. She explores pagan winter festivals, the nativity story, `Sir Charles Dickings' and today's obsession with Santa. Diane Morgan stars.(n)

programme.title: Kevin Bridges: A Whole Different Story
programme.desc: The comedian on stage at Glasgow's SSE Hydro during his 2015 stand-up tour. He entertains 12,000 fans with his thoughts on economic theory, art history and diet tips, as well as politics and the Scottish referendum. He also deals with the rigours of growing up and adapting to his new-found place in the world - coupled with the added novelty of having money for the first time.(n)

programme.title: A Gert Lush Christmas
programme.desc: Regular guy Dan Colman is about to introduce the woman of his dreams, Lisa, to his crazy but adorable Bristolian family at Christmas. But with his fitness-obsessed dad, party animal Uncle Tony, inappropriate brother Jake, and lovely but bonkers mum, it may not go according to plan. Comedy drama, co-written by and starring Russell Howard, with Neil Morrissey and Sophie Thompson.(n)

programme.title: Dragons' Den
programme.desc: Evan Davis presents a Christmas edition of the business show. A Scottish entrepreneur comes bearing gifts of chocolate, a couple of city slickers are selling socks and a teacher hopes to get the party started with his dance mats. Will Peter Jones, Deborah Meaden, Touker Suleyman, Sarah Willingham and Nick Jenkins be feeling generous in this season of goodwill?.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off

In this first of two editions, Mary-Anne Boermans, Ali Imdad, Cathryn Dresser and Norman Calder face three festive challenges, starting with a signature featuring highly decorative Christmas bakes that require intricate icing, a technical that is to be decorated with chocolate snowflakes, and the showstopper, where the bakers must produce a festive masterpiece.(n)

programme.title: Doctor Who
programme.desc: The Doctor spends Christmas in New York, but this time he is not the only hero in town. A deadly alien menace is poised to attack the city, and the Time Lord will need all the help he can get to stop it. Fortunately, Manhattan has its own protector in the form of a mysterious masked superhero (Orphan Black's Justin Chatwin). Peter Capaldi returns for his third Christmas special, currently between companions. He is joined by Matt Lucas, reprising his role from last year's festive episode, and Wolf Hall star Charity Wakefield.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.sub-title: Meerkats: Secrets of an Animal Superstar.

David Attenborough narrates the full story of the research, from the early days when it was a challenge to even get close to a meerkat to the latest revelations about these animals and their complex lives.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The London and South East region's two highest-scoring chefs cook for judges Oliver Peyton, Prue Leith and Matthew Fort. Joining the trio of arbiters in the chamber is award-winning food writer Kevin Gould, who has also been a chef, a grocer and a restaurateur. One contender will be chosen to represent the region in the national finals, taking them a step closer to cooking at the banquet at the Palace of Westminster.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The first of the North East heats sees Mini Patel, Chris Archer and Tommy Banks prepare their starters for the banquet celebrating ordinary Britons honoured by the Queen. Chris is making his debut on the show and produces an entirely gold dish, while Tommy, a self-taught chef with a Michelin star, brings several ingredients grown on his farm in North Yorkshire.(n)

programme.title: Short Circuit
programme.desc: A military robot is struck by lightning and develops a mind of its own. The machine embarks on a series of comic misadventures, but the company that made him want him back. He realises his only hope is to convince the scientist who invented him that he really is alive. Sci-fi comedy adventure, starring Steve Guttenberg, Ally Sheedy and Fisher Stevens.(n)

programme.title: This Farming Life
programme.desc: Summer arrives, and in the east of Scotland, Martin prepares two young bulls for the biggest event of the farming calendar - the Royal Highland Show in Edinburgh. First they need their nose rings, an accessory no bull can do without. Martin and Mel's wedding is also looming, and while he goes for his final kilt fitting, Mel meets her Dad to discuss their plans.(n)

programme.title: Money for Nothing
programme.desc: Entrepreneur Sarah Moore saves a chair, some bits of hawthorn wood, an old art deco style toy and a broken table from the nation's tips. She then sets about transforming them, with the help of three talented artisans, into brand new items ready to be put up for sale.(n)

programme.title: 84 Charing Cross Road
programme.desc: An outspoken writer from New York reminisces about her correspondence of many years with an antiquarian bookseller in London, which began as a business arrangement and developed into a close relationship. Romantic drama based on the real-life experiences of Helene Hanff, starring Anne Bancroft, Anthony Hopkins, Judi Dench and Maurice Denham.(n)

programme.title: Ladies in Lavender
programme.desc: The lives of two elderly spinster sisters are thrown into turmoil when a handsome Polish castaway washes up on the shore by their Cornish home and reawakens long-dormant yearnings and memories. Period drama directed by Charles Dance, starring Judi Dench, Maggie Smith, Daniel Bruhl, Miriam Margolyes, Natascha McElhone and Freddie Jones.(n)

programme.title: Nature's Weirdest Events
programme.desc: Chris Packham presents more mysteries and strange stories, including the strange balls of worms that turned up on a road, fish stuck in fences in Texas and how an Australian town became plagued by giant bats. Plus, why so many sperm whales became stranded around the North Sea in 2015, how a robot could help save the Great Barrier Reef and how a spider in the Sahara could help take humans to other planets.(n)

programme.title: Inside the Factory
programme.desc: Gregg Wallace helps to unload 27 tonnes of dried haricot beans from North America, and follows them on a one-and-a-half mile journey through the largest baked bean factory in the world. Meanwhile, Cherry Healey follows a discarded baked bean can through a recycling centre and on to the largest steelworks in the UK, and historian Ruth Goodman reveals how tinned food was invented to improve sailors' nutrition.(n)

programme.title: Flog It

programme.title: The Marvellous World of Roald Dahl
programme.desc: Documentary, making use of archived letters, writings and biographical material to tell the story of the life of Roald Dahl, in his own inimitable voice. From his time as a fighter pilot in the Second World War, through to his work as a spy and his encounters with Walt Disney and Theodore Roosevelt, the programme explores how Dahl's personal experiences may have informed the fantastical tales he would eventually publish, including Charlie and the Chocolate Factory and Matilda. Includes contributions by Dahl's last wife Liccy, his daughter Lucy and biographer Donald Sturrock. Long-term collaborator Quentin Blake also provides new animated illustrations based on the events of Dahl's life.(n)

programme.title: Roald Dahl's Esio Trot
programme.desc: Hollywood heavyweights Dustin Hoffman and Judi Dench head the cast in this adaptation of Roald Dahl's story about retired bachelor Mr Hoppy, who harbours a secret passion for his neighbour Mrs Silver. Tongue-tied and shy, his attempts to talk to her only end in disaster - and it doesn't help that she lavishes all her affection on another - her pet tortoise Alfie. However, when he discovers her greatest wish is for Alfie to be a little bit bigger, he hits upon a devious idea to finally win her love. Drama, co-starring James Corden and Richard Cordery. Adapted by Richard Curtis and Paul Mayhew-Archer.(n)

programme.title: Judi Dench: All the World's Her Stage
programme.desc: Documentary celebrating the life and times of the veteran actress, looking back at the high points of her 60-year career. Billy Connolly recalls the time, when filming Mrs Brown, he thought she was falling in love with him, Samantha Bond remembers how she calmed Pierce Brosnan's nerves to prepare him for his first scene with the actress, while Harvey Weinstein reveals how Dame Judi honoured him with a `tattoo'. Other contributors include Daniel Craig, Ann Mitchell, Sam Mendes and Ian McKellen. Narrated by Colin Salmon.(n)

programme.title: The Real Marigold Hotel
programme.sub-title: The Real Marigold on Tour: Japan.
programme.desc: Part two of two. The group go East to experience living like Japanese retirees. With one of the longest life expectancies in the world, Miriam Margolyes, Wayne Sleep, Bobby George and Rosemary Shrager search for the secrets of longevity. In the city of Kyoto, they move into a homestay with 73-year-old twin sisters, and start their day with an early morning keep fit class called Radio Taiso.(n)

programme.title: QI
programme.desc: Comedian, novelist and presenter David Baddiel, comedian, actress and writer Cariad Lloyd and stand-up comedian and actor Ross Noble join regular panellist Alan Davies and recently installed host Sandi Toksvig to contemplate questions and facts on the theme `nature and nurture'. As usual, correctness and even intelligence go out of the window in this quiz, in which the questions are so difficult to crack that points are instead awarded for the answers its questionmaster finds most interesting.(n)

programme.title: Dara O Briain Crowd Tickler
programme.desc: The Irish comedian performs at the Hammersmith Apollo, as part of his 2015 tour. Not surprisingly, he leads the audience on a rip-roaring journey through expertly crafted routines, cracking one-liners and the lighting-fast spontaneous gag-making that makes him one of the top exponents of the craft on the circuit at the moment.(n)

programme.title: Stag
programme.desc: Timid schoolteacher Ian Telford finds himself tagging along on his brother-in-law Johnners stag-do; a deer-stalking expedition in the Scottish Highlands. With a gaggle of Johnners' obnoxious friends in tow, Ian quickly discovers the remote wilds can transform the hunters into the hunted, and as sordid secrets emerge, old friendships are tested to the limit. Black comedy, starring Jim Howick and Stephen Campbell Moore.(n)

programme.title: Digging for Britain
programme.desc: Alice Roberts visits archaeological digs in the east of Britain. Finds include new revelations from a 3,000 year old perfectly preserved village near Cambridgeshire, and the theatre where Shakespeare premiered Rome and Juliet.(n)

programme.title: King George & Queen Mary: The Royals Who Rescued the Monarchy
programme.desc: The first of two documentaries providing an insight into the lives of George V and Queen Mary, revealing their lasting influence on Britain's monarchy. The opening film focuses on King George, highlighting how a Victorian-age conservative ended up becoming an unlikely moderniser. The outbreak of the First World War prompted George to reconsider the solidarity of Europe's royal families, leading him to create the House of Windsor and embrace democratic reform. The programme also explores his strained relationship with his children, and the contrasting kinship he found with his granddaughter Princess Elizabeth.(n)

programme.title: Flying Scotsman - From the Footplate
programme.desc: A guide to life on the footplate of the nation's favourite steam engine. Cameras are placed aboad locomotive 60103 as it travels along the Severn Valley, cutting through stunning landscapes on a journey from Bridgnorth to Kidderminster. The `cab cameras' capture veteran driver Roger Norfolk and fireman Ryan Green in action as they talk through the mechanics and challenges of operating this national treasure. Needless to say, things sometimes get hot on the footplate and not everything goes exactly to plan.(n)

programme.title: The Queen Mary: Greatest Ocean Liner
programme.desc: Documentary exploring the life of the Clyde-built ship, from the maiden voyage in May 1936 to New York, and her 1939 role in the Battle of the Atlantic, to her current status as a floating luxury hotel and museum in Long Beach, California. Among the contributors are singer Johnny Mathis.(n)

programme.title: Billy Fury: The Sound of Fury
programme.desc: Liverpool-born Ronnie Wycherley became an overnight sensation in 1958 when he was asked by showbiz impresario Larry Parnes to go on stage and sing a couple of his self-penned songs. Ronnie's knees shook with nerves, but over 2,000 screaming girls welcomed the new star of British rock 'n' roll. Parnes immediately signed Ronnie to his stable of artists and christened him Billy Fury. This documentary recounts Fury's story, and his impact on the birth of popular music in Britain. Contributors include David Puttnam, Mark Kermode, Amanda Barrie, Vince Eager and Imelda May.(n)

programme.sub-title: James May: The Christmas Reassembler: Toy Train Set.
programme.desc: James explores the intricacies and engineering marvels of various objects by putting them together again from a pile of their component parts.(n)

programme.title: Rome's Invisible City
programme.desc: Alexander Armstrong is joined by Dr Michael Scott to explore the underground treasures that made Rome the powerhouse of the ancient world. Using 3D scanning technology, he uncovers the lost subterranean world of the Colosseum, as well as the aqueducts and sewers that supplied and cleansed it, and helped run civilisation's first metropolis and its empire.(n)

programme.title: King George & Queen Mary: The Royals Who Rescued the Monarchy
programme.desc: The first of two documentaries providing an insight into the lives of George V and Queen Mary, revealing their lasting influence on Britain's monarchy. The outbreak of the First World War prompted George to reconsider the solidarity of Europe's royal families, leading him to create the House of Windsor and embrace democratic reform. programme.desc: Simon Bates introduces performances by Shalamar, Soft Cell, Shakin' Stevens, Yazoo, Junior, Lionel Richie, the Jam, Renee & Renato, and David Bowie & Bing Crosby. First shown on 9 December 1982.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: David Jensen introduces performances by the Maisonettes, David Bowie & Bing Crosby, Incantation, Shakin' Stevens, Imagination, Abba, Keith Harris & Orville, Renee & Renato and Modern Romance. First shown on 23 December 1982.(n)

programme.title: King George & Queen Mary: The Royals Who Rescued the Monarchy
programme.desc: Part two of two. Queen Mary's rise from a comparatively low position within the royal hierarchy. She was selected as a potential future wife to the monarch by Queen Victoria when still a child and was first betrothed to Prince Eddy, heir to the throne. After his death she was unceremoniously passed onto his brother George, and following her husband's death in 1935 she emerged as an eccentric yet determined royal matriarch.(n)

programme.desc: Documentary exploring the history of the British TV sitcom, from Hancock's Half Hour in the 1950s to the present day, revealing the inspiration behind some of the most enduring characters and how comedy has reflected changing attitudes in society. In Australia, the Radfords meet that nation's biggest family, the Bonnells, who have 16 kids but enforce much stricter house rules. As the Radfords explore Australia's Gold Coast, cooking kangaroo pies for their hosts and falling out with each other on the other side of the world.(n)

programme.desc: Bio-documentary setting out to reveal the man behind the music, featuring home video from his youth, and footage from his early years performing solo in Greenwich Village. In intimate conversation, Bruce explores the seminal moments that fuelled his relentless drive to become a musician and which have provided the influence for some of the most critically acclaimed and loved songs of the last 50 years. He also talks about his first foray into prose writing with his autobiography, Born to Run, and explains his greatest influences, detailing the people and places that have inspired him and what motivates him to continue to tour and write.(n)

At the same time government-produced public information films petrified viewers with scary scenarios of possible accidents in the home. Contributors include Robin Askwith, Liza Goddard, Oona King, Clive Anderson, Philippa Perry, Samira Ahmed, Ellie Taylor and Angela Barnes.(n)

Thriller, the conclusion of the trilogy based on Stieg Larsson's novels, starring Noomi Rapace and Michael Nyqvist. In Swedish.(n)

The ghost of Christmas past, King George III, tries to get Wills to see the light and rescind the crown back by showing him what Christmas Future will involve if he doesn't. Paul Whitehouse guest stars, with Harry Enfield, Hugh Skinner and Richard Goulding.(n)

programme.title: Biggest Dog in the World
programme.desc: Documentary meeting three households with Great Danes that definitely live up to their names. Essex woman Claire, whose canine companion is so huge, potential boyfriends do a runner once they see him, a US family who had to super-size their lives to accommodate Rocko, and Welshwoman Julie, who paid a high price for her 20-year canine obsession when her marriage ended. The film also reveals the pros and cons of owning giant dogs, including the crippling costs of more than £12,000 a year, constant care for a pet that cannot be left for longer than four hours at a time and extreme domestic destruction.(n)

programme.title: The Adele Story
programme.desc: Documentary charting the remarkable career trajectory of Adele Adkins, the pop and soul singer who rose from humble beginning in Tottenham to become one of the biggest stars of the modern music industry. Now popular enough to warrant going by her forename only, Adele's interest in music was encouraged by her mother from an early age. Winning a place at the Brit School in Croydon, Adele first shot into the public eye when her friend uploaded a demo to MySpace in 2006, and by the time she graduated, the singer had already secured a record deal. What followed were three hugely successful albums, 19, 21 and 25, each of which surpassed the last in terms of critical acclaim and sales figures. Adele also scored an Oscar in 2013 for her song Skyfall, which featured as the theme of the James Bond film of the same name.(n)

programme.title: World's Greatest Divas
programme.desc: A celebration of leading female vocalists whose outstanding talent and big voices are matched by their serious attitudes and even more serious wardrobes. Singers Channel 5 are paying tribute to include the likes of Mariah Carey, Dusty Springfield, Shirley Bassey, Adele and Diana Ross.(n)

programme.title: Lip Sync Battle UK
programme.sub-title: Lip Sync Battle UK Xmas Special.
programme.desc: Shane Richie and Jessie Wallace, also known to EastEnders fans as Alfie and Kat Moon, have a bit of fun for a change in this festive special of the musical challenge, lip-synching to a couple of Christmas songs each - complete with dance moves, facial expressions and costumes. Presented by former Spice Girl Mel B, with help from rapper Professor Green.(n)

programme.title: SuperCasino
programme.desc: Viewers get the chance to take part in live interactive gaming, with an entertaining mix of roulette-wheel spins and lively chat from the presenting team. Featuring a variety of prizes and promotions.(n)

programme.title: Building the Ice Hotel
programme.desc: Documentary following the progress of artistic director Ake Larson and architect Arne Bergh as they embark on a six-week project to build Icehotel, a sophisticated structure constructed in the Swedish village of Jukkasjarvi - more than 120 miles inside the Arctic Circle. The venue has been built from snow and ice every year since 1990, when an edifice housing an exhibition of ice sculptures became a temporary hostel for visiting art enthusiasts. However, an unseasonable heatwave in the middle of the build leaves the team struggling to complete the construction in time to accommodate paying guests.(n)

programme.title: Witch Hunt: A Century of Murder
programme.desc: Suzannah Lipscomb's investigation into the notorious 17th-century witch trials concludes with a profile of Matthew Hopkins, the opportunistic puritan witch-hunter who transformed paranoia about Satanism into a lucrative business as he hanged hundreds of people for crimes they could not possibly have committed. Making use of contemporary reports, Suzannah paints a portrait of a man who believed he could cross any boundary and break any law to achieve his goals. Naming himself `Witchfinder General', Hopkins toured the country charging fees for his services, but Suzannah's research reveals that ultimately, the public's distaste for witches was not as strong as its hatred of being conned by charlatans. Hopkins would eventually die of tuberculosis in relative obscurity, but his malign legacy lived on across the Atlantic, as witch-hunts began in Salem, Massachusetts.(n)

programme.title: Great Artists
programme.desc: Tim Marlow charts the life and work of celebrated Renaissance sculptor, architect and painter Michelangelo, most famous for the extraordinary scenes that adorn the ceiling of the Sistine Chapel in the Vatican.(n)

programme.title: House Doctor
programme.desc: Alistair Appleton presents as interior design expert Ann Maurice casts her eye over a cluttered home in Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire. Unfinished paintwork and dated details are among the factors giving the property a `youth hostel' feel, which despite the asking price being lowered three times is still on the market after six months.(n)

programme.title: House Doctor
programme.desc: Ann Maurice and Alistair Appleton tackle a cottage in Kirk Merrington, Co Durham, that has been on the market for eight months. The property is full of items that remind the owner of her late husband, and interior design expert Ann declares that they are the main problem as no prospective buyers can imagine making the place their own.(n)

programme.title: The WotWots
programme.desc: The aliens learn about creatures that hang upside down.(n)

programme.title: Lily's Driftwood Bay
programme.desc: Lily and Bull get very lost on a camping trip when they follow a little flying light.(n)

programme.desc: Pontypandy Fire Station is opened to the public and Norman is eager to try things out, crawling under safety tape and getting into the driving seat of a fire engine. However, his inquisitive nature and desire for excitement lead to danger when he climbs onto the roof to get closer to Tom and his helicopter.(n)

programme.desc: The youngster is unhappy to discover she has nits and everyone makes sure they keep out of her way. Narrated by Julian Clary.(n)

programme.desc: Rehearsals for Pip and Alba's new play about pirates are in full swing when the Mice Pirates sail into harbour. Cap'n Bilge mistakes the actors for rival treasure-hunters and throws the players and their audience into chaos by ordering his mice to invade the stage.(n)

programme.desc: Kevin gets trapped by a roof-fall of snow, but Victor thinks that he has gone to the depot and sets out to rescue him.(n)

programme.desc: Peppa pays a visit to Aunty and Uncle Pig, and discovers Cousin Chloe has a new puppet theatre.(n)

programme.desc: The youngster tries to get Daddy Pig fit and healthy.(n)

programme.desc: Cap'n Turbot and his cousin Francois go deep-sea diving to take a picture of a rare sea slug, but their diving bell ends up getting stuck.(n)

programme.title: Toot the Tiny Tugboat
programme.desc: The tiny boat tries to help Paula overcome her embarrassment when she makes a mistake.(n)

programme.title: Toby's Travelling Circus
programme.desc: The posters advertising the circus are blown away in the wind and a fallen pole blocks the lane, leaving the gang wondering whether anyone will turn up for the show.(n)

programme.title: Jelly Jamm
programme.desc: Rita finds an injured dodo, which she takes home to nurse.(n)

programme.title: SpongeBob SquarePants
programme.desc: Double bill. SpongeBob must recover a stolen secret ingredient, and Plankton is surprised to discover someone actually likes his food.(n)

programme.title: World's Strongest Man 2016
programme.desc: Action from the third heat of the competition at Chobe National Park, Botswana. Iceland's Hafthor `Thor' Bjornsson - known to viewers of Game of Thrones as the mighty Mountain - took part alongside Britain's Terry Hollands, who spent the 2015 event on the other side of the fence, providing analysis for Channel 5. Presented by James Richardson, Sarah-Jane Crawford and former strongman competitor Magnus Ver Magnusson, with commentary from Danny Wallace and Colin Bryce.(n)

programme.title: Make You Laugh Out Loud
programme.sub-title: Penguins Make You Laugh Out Loud.
programme.desc: Documentary featuring the flightless birds at their funniest, led by social media star Spike. A resident of Birdland in the Cotswolds, the king penguin has featured in many ad campaigns and has also become famous on the internet for his penguin pratfalls. Despite the title, the programme also features other animals, including the camel that got a little too close for comfort to a family in Kansas, and the Wicklow seal that has trained local fishmongers to feed it. With comic contributions from Dave Spikey, Felicity Ward and Bobby Mare.(n)

programme.title: Make You Laugh Out Loud
programme.desc: Comedians Zoe Lyons, Ellie Taylor and Marlon Davis present a seasonal clip show featuring some of the funniest Christmas-themed videos currently doing the rounds online. Among the disastrous 'Santa fails', Christmas dinner disasters and grumpy dressed-up pets, the trio also highlight the stories behind popular yuletide videos, including the story of the bearded shopper who decided to play along when a three-year-old passer-by mistook him for Father Christmas, and Norman the bull mastiff, who hates Christmas and all associated songs. Narrated by Iain Lee.(n)

programme.title: Make You Laugh Out Loud
programme.sub-title: Christmas Makes You Laugh Out Loud.
programme.desc: Iain Lee narrates a compilation of amusing and outrageous Christmas-themed videos that have taken the internet by storm in a seasonal special showcasing hilarious online clips with a festive twist. Examples include the unpredictable reactions of youngsters, from the adorable moment a young boy catches Santa Claus delivering presents on his webcam to the tantrum to end all tantrums thrown by one child who does not receive the gifts he was expecting.(n)

programme.title: Labyrinth
programme.desc: A teenager wishes her baby brother would be taken away, only to have her request granted by a band of goblins and their sinister king. She regrets her decision and sets out to rescue him, but to reach the castle where he is being held, she must find her way through a magical maze full of strange creatures. Jim Henson's fantasy adventure, starring Jennifer Connelly and David Bowie.(n)

programme.title: Planet of the Apes
programme.desc: An astronaut crash-lands on a strange planet and is captured and enslaved by the ruling race of highly intelligent apes. Luckily, he is helped by a sympathetic chimpanzee - but then discovers a shocking secret. Remake of the 1960s sci-fi adventure, directed by Tim Burton and starring Mark Wahlberg, Helena Bonham Carter and Tim Roth, and featuring a cameo appearance from the original film's star Charlton Heston. Includes 5 News Update at 5.00pm.(n)

programme.title: BattleBots
programme.sub-title: BattleBots: World Championship: Last Chance to Advance - Round of 16 Part Two.
programme.desc: Molly McGrath introduces four more three-minute battles in the arena, to decide which teams will be going through to the next round.(n)

programme.title: World's Strongest Man 2016
programme.desc: Action from the fourth heat of the competition at Chobe National Park in Botswana. Britain's Laurence Shahlaei took part, having previously retired from the sport due to injury, and faced the likes of Canadian Jean-Francois Caron in his group. Presented by James Richardson, Sarah-Jane Crawford and former strongman competitor Magnus Ver Magnusson, with commentary from Danny Wallace and Colin Bryce.(n)

programme.title: Britain's Cleverest Dog
programme.desc: Brainbox pets and others animals, from a canine Einstein that makes the news after mastering a shape-sorting puzzle that most toddlers struggle with to a prize pooch entered into a competition for trick dogs. Scientific research is also proving how supposedly dumb animals like goats and donkeys are cleverer than people might think. This is demonstrated by a Kent woman who has taught her pet raccoon a remarkable range of skills, such as pushing a toddler's scooter and even riding a bicycle.(n)

programme.title: Flowers in the Attic 2: Petals on the Wind
programme.desc: Premiere. A woman trapped in an abusive relationship is forced to face up to the traumatic events of her childhood and her incestuous feelings for her brother. Following a tragedy, she returns to the family home, intending to take revenge on her mother by seducing her husband. Drama based on the second in VC Andrews' series of novels, starring Heather Graham, Rose McIver and Ellen Burstyn. Includes 5 News Update at 10.00.(n)

programme.title: The Blind Side
programme.desc: A middle-class family take in a hulking homeless teenager, who has no education or skills to speak of. The indomitable wife encourages him to turn his life around, helping him to get the grades he needs for a college scholarship and hone his sporting skills to become an American football player. Fact-based drama, starring an Oscar-winning Sandra Bullock alongside Quinton Aaron and Tim McGraw.(n)

programme.title: Magic Mike XXL
programme.desc: Retired male stripper Magic Mike decides to help his friends put on one last show, as the crew embark on a road trip to Myrtle Beach to perform at an exotic-dance convention. Along the way, they brighten the lives of several women in this sexy sequel(n)

programme.title: Howard the Duck
programme.desc: Comedy-adventure about a fast-talking, cigar-chomping, beer-loving duck from another dimension who somehow winds up in Cleveland and has run-ins with punk rockers, motorcycle mamas and the all-powerful overlord who make him wish he were back on his own duck planet(n)

programme.title: Halloween: Resurrection
programme.desc: A group of teens win a contest to spend a night in Michael Myers' childhood home which will be broadcast live on the internet. They believe they are in for a little fun and some free publicity but things go terribly wrong and turn into a game of life and death(n)

In this inspiring biopic, Jackie Robinson breaks Major League Baseball's color barrier when he is signed to the Brooklyn Dodgers by the team's forward-thinking general manager, Branch Rickey. The gifted athlete deals with tremendous pressure and threats from racist fans and players, but perseveres to become a legendary baseball player and a heroic figure in American history(n)

programme.title: A Beautiful Mind
programme.desc: Oscar-winning drama based on the true story of prominent mathematician John Forbes Nash Jr, who seemed to be guaranteed a promising future when he won international acclaim as a result of his pioneering work in the field. However, when he is recruited to provide assistance to the military with top-secret code-breaking duties, the high-pressure job begins to take its toll on him and he begins to develop a mental illness(n)

programme.title: The Score
programme.desc: A retiring safecracker considers one last heist, but his partners may be trickier than any combination he's ever solved. A slick, involving caper(n)

programme.title: Run All Night
programme.desc: Liam Neeson reunites with Unknown director Jaume Collet-Serra for this Warner Bros. thriller following a mob hit man and his estranged son (Joel Kinnaman) as they flee the wrath of a vengeful crime boss(n)

programme.title: Dead Presidents
programme.desc: Set between 1968 and 1971, this highly episodic drama focuses on Anthony, a young black man from the Bronx who goes to Vietnam after his high-school graduation. Unable to find a job when he returns from the war, Anthony turns to crime and begins plotting a major theft(n)

programme.title: Godsend
programme.desc: Drama about a couple who make the decision to have their eight-year-old son cloned following his death in a tragic accident. Under the supervision of an expert in stem cell research, their son is illegally cloned, leading to a bizarre series of events(n)

programme.title: 25th Hour
programme.desc: Edward Norton is sensational in director Spike Lee's riveting drama about a drug dealer and his last night of freedom before prison. The film is also a poignant salute to the resilience of New York City in the aftermath of Sept. 11. The strong supporting cast includes Barry Pepper, Rosario Dawson, Philip Seymour Hoffman and ex-football star Tony Siragusa(n)

programme.title: The Score
programme.desc: A retiring safecracker considers one last heist, but his partners may be trickier than any combination he's ever solved. A slick, involving caper(n)

programme.title: American Pie 2
programme.desc: The entire ensemble cast from the original smash-hit sex comedy returns for this even more outrageous sequel. After their first year of college, Jim (Jason Biggs) and his randy pals rent a beach house for summer fun and games. When Jim learns that gorgeous exchange student Nadia (Shannon Elizabeth) will be paying a visit, he decides to get some quick lessons in love. Alyson Hannigan, Chris Klein(n)

programme.title: Perkins' 14
programme.desc: Dark Ride director Craig Singer returns to the helm with this shocking horror film about a delusional psychopath who creates a unified team of 14 maniacal killers. Produced entirely over the Internet, where writers uploaded story details and actors submitted audition tapes, Perkins' 14 was released into theaters as part of the third After Dark Horror Fest. Ronald Perkins was just six years old when his parents were brutally slaughtered right before his eyes. Unable to overcome the incredible trauma of witnessing such a diabolical event, Perkins becomes convinced that the killers who murdered his parents will eventually return to finish the job they started years ago -- and he plans to be fully prepared to fight back when they do. Years later, when Perkins turns 34, he kidnaps 14 people from his hometown of Stone Cove and sets about reprogramming them to become relentless killing machines. Now, if the killers ever do return, they'll have to get through Perkins' 14 in order to reach their intended target. Trouble is, now that Perkins' 14 are ready for battle, they've become increasingly difficult to contain(n)

programme.title: The Order
programme.desc: Heath Ledger stars as a renegade Catholic priest who uncovers a dark secret in the Church while investigating the death of his mentor in this spine-tingling religious thriller. The script was written by director Brian Helgeland, who penned the Oscar-winning "L.A. Confidential." He also worked with Ledger and costars Shannyn Sossamon and Mark Addy in "A Knight's Tale." Benno Furmann, Peter Weller, Francesco Carnelutti(n)

programme.title: Broadcast News
programme.desc: Tom Grunick is the slow-thinking, good-looking TV anchorman competing alongside reporter Aaron Altman for the heart of sharp cookie producer Jane Craig(n)

programme.title: Focus
programme.desc: In this fast-paced caper, a con artist takes on an inexperienced apprentice, but struggles to keep his eyes on the prize when he develops romantic feelings for her(n)

programme.title: Consenting Adults
programme.desc: A wealthy couple befriend their new neighbours, but do the newcomers have ulterior motives for their friendship?(n)

programme.title: Presumed Innocent
programme.desc: When the female deputy prosecutor R.K. Sabich had an affair with is murdered the prosecutor asks him to lead the investigation. When Sabich digs too deeply he finds himself framed for the murder(n)

programme.title: Fracture
programme.desc: Anthony Hopkins, Ryan Gosling and David Strathairn star in Gregory Hoblit's twist-filled legal drama. When top airplane engineer Ted Crawford discovers that his wife has been cheating on him he takes a devastatingly direct route to revenge: he drives home and shoots his errant spouse in the face. He then waits for the police to turn up and confesses to the crime. With his wife in a coma, Crawford is arrested and enters the justice system. It should, of course, be the simplest prosecution ever. And lawyer Willy Beachum can be forgiven for thinking that his last case as a criminal attorney (before he switches to company law) is set to be a doddle. However, once the case comes to court, Crawford, representing himself, proceeds to tear apart the ample evidence that's stacked against him. Can he possibly get away with his crime? Also starring Rosamund Pike, Billy Burke and Fiona Shaw(n)

programme.title: Jurassic World
programme.desc: In this thrilling fourth installment of the "Jurassic Park" franchise, two young brothers visit an aunt who's an executive at Jurassic World, a theme park populated with genetically resurrected dinosaurs. But chaos erupts when a newly created dino escapes its enclosure, forcing the park's animal behaviorist to save the day(n)

programme.title: Shaft
programme.desc: This action drama puts a new spin on Shaft, one of the key "blaxploitation" films of the 1970s. John Shaft (Samuel L. Jackson), the namesake nephew of the legendary private eye (Richard Roundtree), is a street-smart police detective who with his partner Carmen Velez (Vanessa L. Williams) has been assigned to a racially motivated murder case, in which a black college student was killed in front of a restaurant by Walter Williams Jr. (Christian Bale), the sociopathic son of a New York construction tycoon, who then fled the country rather than face prosecution. Diane Palmieri (Toni Collette), a waitress on a smoke break, saw the murder, but she doesn't want to talk to the police. Two years later, Walter is forced to return to New York, but without Diane's testimony, the city doesn't have much of a case. Soon, Shaft, Walter Junior, and Walter Senior's goons are all looking for Diane, with Junior enlisting the help of Peoples Hernandez (Jeffrey Wright), a small-time drug dealer who will do anything to move into the big leagues. Shaft and Carmen find Diane, but discover that she had a good reason for being on the lam for the past two years. Amidst all this activity, John gets frequent advice from his uncle, with whom he ponders the idea of quitting the force and opening a detective agency. Shaft was directed by John Singleton, from a screenplay by Singleton, Richard Price, and Shane Salerno(n)

programme.desc: Tight-knit gang of street racers battle a new nemesis and rescue a software genius from terrorists(n)

programme.title: India's Deadliest Snakes
programme.desc: Romulus Whitaker, a snake expert with more than 40 years of field experience, sets out to discover the truth behind a reported rise in snake-bites in India, which may have caused more human deaths than the official statistics suggest. He investigates some of the subcontinent's deadliest reptiles, including the king cobra and sawscaled viper, and explores the natural history that has led to this epidemic.(n)

programme.title: Wonders of the Monsoon
programme.desc: Documentary examining the plants and animals that thrive in monsoon areas, narrated by Colin Salmon. Crested black macaques take advantage of an abundance of fruit, and maleo birds use the sun to incubate their eggs on the Indonesian island of Sulawesi. On Java, locals climb volcanoes to offer live sacrifices in thanks for the peaks' help in precipitating rain and fertilising plants with ash. The frequent and heavy rains in Borneo have destroyed the soils, created fierce competition for scarce nutrients, and driven evolution to produce some curious creatures. The Rajah Brooke's pitcher encourages tree shrews to relieve themselves to obtain the substances it needs, while the Bornean red leech is capable of swallowing the giant blue earthworm in one gulp.(n)

programme.title: Wonders of the Monsoon
programme.desc: Exploring the relationship that has developed over thousands of years between the people who live in monsoon regions and the wildlife they share them with. In the rice paddies of Assam, India, farmers battle a herd of hungry elephants over their crops, while on the Philippine island of Palawan, near Borneo, people still hunt in the forest and live in caves for part of the year. The programme also looks at the impact of organised religion, meeting members of the Bishnoi sect who believe that all life is sacred and have even been known to lay down their lives to protect trees. Colin Salmon narrates. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Wonders of the Monsoon
programme.desc: Colin Salmon narrates a documentary exploring how the lives of humans and animals across a vast area of the planet are affected by the transforming power of the monsoon rains. The end of the dry season in northern Australia sees 300,000 flying foxes gathering to drink while running a gauntlet of freshwater crocodiles, while in Sumatra a female orang-utan guides her youngster to where she knows a fig tree fruits at this time of year. At the Delhi stock exchange, the price of rice escalates every day the rains fail to materialise and priests submerge themselves in water and beseech Varuna, god of water, to come.(n)

programme.title: Wonders of the Monsoon
programme.desc: The effect of the rainy season on wildlife in Asia, with floods forcing animals to flee from Kaziranga National Park in north-east India in search of the safety of the hills. In Cambodia, the Mekong river swells so much that water is forced back up one of its tributaries to fill the vast Tonle Sap lake - one of the most productive freshwater fisheries on Earth. Fresh grass draws nomads and their vast herds of livestock back to their homelands, but they are stalked by hungry wolves and hyenas, which move in at night for the kill. Colin Salmon narrates.(n)

programme.title: Wonders of the Monsoon
programme.desc: The other side of the monsoon, as the winds bring dry air and drought. Budgerigars swarm in the Australian desert, gathering at a precious waterhole, and although birds of prey try to ambush them, they are mesmerised by the array of bright colours on show. On the island of Borneo, a bearded pig hunts for seafood on the beach, while in the Rajasthan desert, nomads haggle over the price of camels, which can provide vital transport during this lean season. The mugger crocodiles of Sri Lanka stalk the animals taking a much-needed drink and a young leopard learning to hunt discovers there is no such thing as an easy meal. Colin Salmon narrates.(n)

programme.title: South Pacific
programme.desc: An exploration of the effects of the eruption of volcanos in the ocean. From these violent beginnings emerge islands and coral reefs that are home to a vast array of wildlife, including giant manta rays and vampire bugs that thrive in the tropical snow, after a process that takes millions of years. Benedict Cumberbatch narrates.(n)

programme.title: South Pacific
programme.desc: The struggle for survival on the region's isolated islands, home to flightless parrots, burrowing bats, giant skinks and tree-dwelling kangaroos. The documentary reveals how the arrival of new species can upset the delicate natural balance, with disastrous consequences, and explores the human history of the region. Benedict Cumberbatch narrates.(n)

programme.title: South Pacific
programme.desc: Efforts to preserve the marine life of the region, which is home to the world's richest coral reefs and an array of species, including whales, sharks, albatross and tuna. Despite millions of people relying on its fish stocks, the seas have very little protection and face various threats, with international fishing fleets taking a disastrous toll. Benedict Cumberbatch narrates. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: South Pacific
programme.desc: Documentary exploring the region's islands, which are home to a vast array of extraordinary wildlife. The programme reveals how remote human communities native to the area are surrounded by harsh terrain and subjected to extreme weather conditions. Benedict Cumberbatch narrates.(n)

programme.title: South Pacific
programme.desc: A look at how the 20,000 islands in the region became colonised by humans and animals. For the Polynesians, the Pacific's first people, their journeys constituted a feat of navigational ingenuity, while animals often had to rely on violent forces of nature, such as cyclones and tsunamis, to reach the shores.(n)

programme.title: South Pacific
programme.desc: An exploration of the marine wildlife of the region. programme.title: Bulletproof Monk
programme.desc: Chow Yun-Fat stars as an ageless Tibetan monk whose task is to guard the mystical Scroll of the Ultimate from modern-day Nazis. He rescued the scroll from their clutches in 1943, denying them victory in the war, but the fascists still want it so the Third Reich can rise again. In modern-day New York, the monk finds an apprentice in the unlikely guise of Kar, a punk pickpocket. He teaches him both the history of the scroll and the martial arts skills he will need to defend it, as the pair have to fend off the enemy, who are beginning to close in. Paul Hunter's all-action film also stars Jaime King as Scott's love interest and Victoria Smurfit as the fanatical granddaughter of Nazi Strucker(n)

programme.title: Paul Blart: Mall Cop 2
programme.desc: Everyone's favorite bumbling mall cop returns in this sequel from Happy Madison and director Andy Fickman. Original Paul Blart: Mall Cop screenwriters Kevin James and Nick Bakay reteam to pen the script, which finds Paul Blart (James) and his daughter Maya in Las Vegas for a security-guard expo. When a band of menacing art thieves attempt a daring heist, Blart attempts to stop them with the help of the cynical casino security staff who once ridiculed him. Meanwhile, Blart contends with a crafty rival (Nicholas Turturro)(n)

programme.title: French Kiss
programme.desc: When a woman's fiancé calls from Paris to call their wedding off, the aerophobic gets on a plane where she meets a petty thief who stashes his loot in her luggage to get it through customs(n)

programme.title: The Money Pit
programme.desc: Walter Fielding and Anna Crowley have to look for a new house - but there's not much they can afford! This changes when they meet a lonely old con-artist who sells them a beautiful mansion at a ridiculously low price. Only there's a catch. The second Walter and Anna move in to the house it falls apart, starting from the stairway, to the bath falling through the roof to eventually the chimney falling into the house! Finally, they have to renovate the house before the frame collapses but the renovations also prove to be a disaster(n)

programme.title: Amistad
programme.desc: This Steven Spielberg-directed exploration into a long-ago episode in African-American history recounts the trial that followed the 1839 rebellion aboard the Spanish slave ship Amistad and captures the complex political maneuverings set in motion by the event. Filmed in New England and Puerto Rico, the 152-minute drama opens with a pre-credit sequence showing Cinque (Djimon Hounsou) and the other Africans in a violent takeover of the Amistad. Captured, they are imprisoned in New England where former slave Theodore Joadson (Morgan Freeman), viewing the rebels as "freedom fighters," approaches property lawyer Baldwin (Matthew McConaughey), who attempts to prove the Africans were "stolen goods" because they were kidnapped. Running for re-election, President Martin Van Buren (Nigel Hawthorne) overturns the lower court's decision in favor of the Africans. Former President John Quincy Adams (Anthony Hopkins) is reluctant to become involved, but when the case moves on to the Supreme Court, Adams stirs emotions with a powerful defense. The storyline occasionally cuts away to Spain where the young Queen Isabella (Anna Paquin) plays with dolls; she later debated the Amistad case with seven U.S. presidents. The character portrayed by Morgan Freeman is a fictional composite of several historical figures. programme.title: Amistad
programme.desc: This Steven Spielberg-directed exploration into a long-ago episode in African-American history recounts the trial that followed the 1839 rebellion aboard the Spanish slave ship Amistad and captures the complex political maneuverings set in motion by the event. Filmed in New England and Puerto Rico, the 152-minute drama opens with a pre-credit sequence showing Cinque (Djimon Hounsou) and the other Africans in a violent takeover of the Amistad. Captured, they are imprisoned in New England where former slave Theodore Joadson (Morgan Freeman), viewing the rebels as "freedom fighters," approaches property lawyer Baldwin (Matthew McConaughey), who attempts to prove the Africans were "stolen goods" because they were kidnapped. Running for re-election, President Martin Van Buren (Nigel Hawthorne) overturns the lower court's decision in favor of the Africans. Former President John Quincy Adams (Anthony Hopkins) is reluctant to become involved, but when the case moves on to the Supreme Court, Adams stirs emotions with a powerful defense. The storyline occasionally cuts away to Spain where the young Queen Isabella (Anna Paquin) plays with dolls; she later debated the Amistad case with seven U.S. presidents. The character portrayed by Morgan Freeman is a fictional composite of several historical figures. For authentic speech, the Africans speak the Mende language, subtitled during some scenes but not others(n)

programme.title: In Her Shoes
programme.desc: Two sisters must set aside their differences to share a surprising discovery in this drama. Maggie Feller (Cameron Diaz) and her sister, Rose (Toni Collette), are two siblings who have practically nothing in common beyond sharing the same shoe size. Maggie is beautiful but was never good in school due to dyslexia, and over the years has learned to use her looks and her charm to get what she wants, at the expense of what others think of her. Rose, on the other hand, is a successful lawyer but has never had much luck in love and has serious self-respect issues. When Maggie finds herself evicted from her apartment, she turns up on Rose's doorstep; Rose grudgingly takes in her sister, but a few uncomfortable weeks together end when Maggie seduces Rose's boyfriend. Maggie once again finds herself on the street until she makes a surprising discovery -- while she and her sister had long believed that their grandmother Ella (Shirley MacLaine) was dead, it turns out she's alive and well and living in Florida. Based on the best-selling novel by Jennifer Weiner, In Her Shoes marked a change of pace for director Curtis Hanson, best known for his taste in hard-edged dramas such as 8 Mile and L.A. programme.desc: When a priceless Monet painting is stolen from the Metropolitan Museum of Art, the police find themselves wondering which world-class art thief pulled the job. What they don't know is that the thief wasn't a professional, but an amateur. Thomas Crown (Pierce Brosnan) was born poor but made his way through Oxford on a boxing scholarship. With his sharp sense for business and ruthless ambition, Crown has become a self-made billionaire; but despite his wealth and power, he still seeks new challenges, and he steals art not for the profits but for the sheer excitement. However, as fun as art theft might be, it's still illegal, and investigator Catherine Banning (Rene Russo) is brought in to track down the culprit. Certain clues point to Crown, so Banning introduces herself into Crown's social circle. Police detective Michael McCann (Denis Leary) warns Banning against getting too close to Crown. She takes McCann's suggestion lightly -- until she finds herself falling for the suave thief.
